          "date": "2016-03-09 03:40:58.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "subject": "LU-6528 mdt: keep FS capability for intent_getattr",
        "message": "LU-6528 mdt: keep FS capability for intent_getattr\n\nWhen \"no_subtree_check\" is set for NFS export, nfsd_set_fh_dentry()\ndoesn't set correct fsuid explicitely, but raise capability to allow\nexportfs_decode_fh() to reconnect disconnected dentry into dcache.\nSo for lookup (i.e. intent_getattr), we should keep FS capability on\nMDS, otherwise it will fail permission check.\n\nThis is a backport from master:\nLustre-commit: I99e2caeec06239a1df39918cbd6e9213e37ec758\nLustre-change: http://review.whamcloud.com/14978\n\nSigned-off-by: Lai Siyao <lai.siyao@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I681fb53c6e93317aa9f7d55ee06987a09fb12afc\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/b2_7"
    }
